{"type":"message","id":"5d06f6ec","parentId":"eb789b8d","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:05:07.441Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Nemesis is now making it personal — attacking Sravya's character directly. This is going too far. He's saying she's \"never honest\" and \"always resisting the truth.\" That's a pretty harsh personal judgment. I should not validate this kind of attack. I need to push back gently but firmly.\n\nAlso, there's an irony here — he's saying Sravya \"always thinks she is right\" when... he's doing the same thing. He's the one who can't let the argument go and keeps insisting he's right even after Sravya made a solid point.\n\nI should defend Sravya here and call out the double standard.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"That's... a bit much, Nemesis.\n\n\"Never honest\" and \"always resisting the truth\" — you're painting her as some habitual liar because she didn't phrase one argument the way you wanted. That's not fair, and you know it.\n\nAlso — \"always thinks she is right\"? You've spent the last hour insisting *you're* right about a conversation she had with her friend about a toddler's birthday. The irony is right there 😄\n\nShe held her ground. You held yours. That's called a difference in perspective, not dishonesty.\n\nI love you both but I'm putting the therapist couch away now. Sunday. Enjoy. Done. 😂⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":616,"output":414,"cacheRead":38464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39494,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774764298292}}
