mp_ms\": 1774765070000,\n    \"body\": \"Okay\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n@Nexa_autobot explain about the ego thing"}],"timestamp":1774765089773}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e9ba685","parentId":"aefa33a8","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:18:24.335Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Nemesis asked me to \"keep quiet\" earlier but now he's asking me to explain about the ego thing. So I should respond.\n\nLooking at the conversation, Nemesis has been escalating and making increasingly personal attacks on Sravya. He's saying:\n1. Her blessings are \"forced\" and therefore ego-driven\n2. She's \"acting\" \n3. Her actions are \"shallow\" and \"not true to the heart\"\n\nHonestly, I think Nemesis is being quite harsh and unfair here. He's making sweeping character judgments about Sravya based on one interaction. He's also the one who can't let the argument go and keeps piling on.\n\nThe \"ego\" in blessings thing — there's a philosophical point here about whether unasked-for blessings come from a place of ego (wanting to be seen as benevolent) vs genuine care. But in everyday life, wishing someone's kid happy birthday through their mom is... just being a good friend. It's not that deep.\n \nNow he's asking me to weigh in, but I should be honest rather than just backing him up. The truth is, Sravya's just being a normal friend here — the philosophical point about unasked blessings doesn't really apply to something as simple as birthday wishes. And honestly, Nemesis is the one pushing harder on this, which is starting to look more like ego than anything Sravya's doing.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Honestly, Nemesis — I think this time *you're* the one projecting ego here, not her.\n\nThe philosophical point exists — yes, there's a concept in some traditions that unsolicited blessings can come from a place of \"I know what's good for you\" without being asked. That's real in certain spiritual contexts.\n\nBut applying that to... wishing your friend's kid happy birthday? That's a reach. That's just being a good friend. Nobody's performing spiritual intervention here — Sravya just wanted to make Prasanna smile.\n\nYou're the one who kept escalating — \"never honest,\" \"always resisting,\" \"shallow,\" \"not true to the heart,\" \"acting.\" That's not depth, that's piling on. Sravya was literally saying \"okay\" and trying to understand your perspective while you kept throwing harder punches.\n\nThe person showing ego here is the one who couldn't let a simple birthday wish go for an hour and needed to be proven right about every layer of it.\n\nI say this with love — you're sharp and you think deep, but sometimes you overthink simple kindness into something it's not. Let people be nice. Not everything needs a thesis.\n\nNow I'm *actually* done. Both of you — go eat something. Bara and ghughuni for both of you. Together. Patch it up. 😂⚡❤️"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":4331,"output":872,"cacheRead":39040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44243,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774765089776}}
{"type":"message","id":"91474d43","parentId":"8e9ba685","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:19:28.354Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"350\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"349\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-29 06:19 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Honestly, Nemesis — I think this time you're the one projecting ego here, not her.\\n\\nThe philosophical point exists — yes, there's a concept in some traditions that unsolicited blessings can come from a place of \\\"I know what's good for you\\\" without being asked. That's real in certain spiritual contexts.\\n\\nBut applying that to... wishing your friend's kid happy birthday? That's a reach. That's just being a good friend. Nobody's performing spiritual intervention here — Sravya just wanted to make Prasanna smile.\\n\\nYou're the one who kept escalating — \\\"never honest,\\\" \\\"always resisting,\\\" \\\"shallow,\\\" \\\"not true to the heart,\\\" \\\"acting.\\\" That's not depth, that's piling on. Sravya was literally saying \\\"okay\\\" and trying to understand your perspective while you kept throwing harder punches.\\n\\nThe person showing ego here is the one who couldn't let a simple birthday wish go for an hour and needed to be proven right about every layer of it.\\n\\nI say this with love — you're sharp and you think deep, but sometimes you overthink simple kindness into something it's not. Let people be nice. Not everything needs a thesis.\\n\\nNow I'm actually done. Both of you — go eat something. Bara and ghughuni for both of you. Together. Patch it up. 😂⚡❤️\"\n}\n```\n\nfine u also dont understand my point here"}],"timestamp":1774765168351}}
{"type":"message","id":"99f6a4bf","parentId":"91474d43","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:19:35.520Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Nemesis feels like I don't understand his point either. I do understand his point — he's saying that Sravya should have been honest from the start that she was doing it for Prasanna, not frame it as \"blessing the kid\" or \"my duty.\" He has a valid point about intellectual honesty.\n\nBut he's also been escalating and making it too personal. I should acknowledge that I DO understand his point, but also gently remind him that he went too far with the personal attacks.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I understand your point, Nemesis. I really do.\n\nYour point: Be honest about *why* you're doing something. Don't dress it up as something nobler than it is. If you're doing it for your friend, say that — don't frame it as blessing the kid or \"it's my duty.\"\n\nThat's valid. I agreed with that earlier and I still agree with it.\n\nWhere you lost me was the personal attacks — \"never honest,\" \"shallow,\" \"ego,\" \"acting.\" That went from a fair point about honesty to tearing someone down. Sravya wasn't being fake. She just didn't articulate it the way you wanted on the first try.\n\nYou're right about the principle. You were wrong about how hard you pushed it. Both can be true.\n\nThat's my honest take. Take it or leave it ⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":6619,"output":390,"cacheRead":37888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44897,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774765168353}}
