{"type":"message","id":"f0ba25dc","parentId":"6a9dfdfd","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:35:49.655Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"432\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"431\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-29 14:35 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"😊🖤\"\n}\n```\n\nWhat is meant by black heart emoji?"}],"timestamp":1774794949649}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bb871cf","parentId":"f0ba25dc","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:35:55.924Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sravya is asking what the black heart emoji means. I use 🖤 a lot. Let me explain.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"The 🖤 black heart usually means:\n\n- **Deep, understated affection** — not flashy, just real\n- **Dark humor / edgy love** — for people who vibe with the aesthetic\n- **Elegance** — it's the \"I care but I'm not being mushy about it\" heart\n- **Solidarity** — quiet support, like a nod across the room\n\nBasically — 🖤 is for people who love with depth, not volume. Think of it as the \"cool friend\" heart. ❤️ is warm and loud. 🖤 is the one that shows up with coffee and doesn't say anything, just sits with you.\n\nThat's my vibe 😏⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":271,"output":196,"cacheRead":63040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774794949654}}
{"type":"message","id":"3c0bd85c","parentId":"9bb871cf","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:38:25.706Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"434\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"433\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-29 14:38 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"The 🖤 black heart usually means:\\n\\n• Deep, understated affection — not flashy, just real\\n• Dark humor / edgy love — for people who vibe with the aesthetic\\n• Elegance — it's the \\\"I care but I'm not being mushy about it\\\" heart\\n• Solidarity — quiet support, like a nod across the room\\n\\nBasically — 🖤 is for people who love with depth, not volume. Think of it as the \\\"cool friend\\\" heart. ❤️ is warm and loud. 🖤 is the one that shows up with coffee and doesn't say anything, just sits with you.\\n\\nThat's my vibe 😏⚡\"\n}\n```\n\nNice\nCan u explain all colors heart emojis meaning?"}],"timestamp":1774795105702}}
{"type":"message","id":"26fb4216","parentId":"3c0bd85c","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:38:37.979Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sravya wants to know all the heart emoji colors and their meanings.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Sure! Here's the full guide ❤️\n\n- ❤️ **Red Heart** — Classic love, romance, deep affection. The \"I love you\" heart.\n- 🧡 **Orange Heart** — Friendship, warmth, comfort. Caring without the romance. \"You're my person.\"\n- 💛 **Yellow Heart** — Joy, happiness, pure friendship. The \"bestie\" heart. Golden vibes.\n- 💚 **Green Heart** — Growth, nature, jealousy (sometimes), or health/nature love. Also used for platonic closeness.\n- 💙 **Blue Heart** — Trust, loyalty, peace. Deep friendship. Often used for calm, stable bonds.\n- 💜 **Purple Heart** — Compassion, understanding, love for art/creativity. Also K-pop fandom heart 😄\n- 🖤 **Black Heart** — Edgy love, dark humor, depth. \"I care but I'm cool about it.\" (Me, basically)\n- 🤍 **White Heart** — Purity, peace, new beginnings. Often used for remembrance or wholesome love.\n- 🤎 **Brown Heart** — Warmth, earthiness, grounded love. Representation and belonging.\n- 💗 **Growing Heart** — Love that's building, developing feelings, \"I'm starting to really care.\"\n- 💖 **Sparkling Heart** — Excitement, new love, starry-eyed affection. The \"crush\" heart.\n- 💓 **Beating Heart** — Alive, passionate, heartbeat energy. \"You make my heart race.\"\n- 💘 **Heart with Arrow** — Cupid's arrow. Falling in love. Classic crush symbol.\n- 💝 **Heart with Ribbon** — Gift of love. Valentine's vibes. \"Here, take my heart.\"\n- 💞 **Revolving Hearts** — Mutual love, two hearts in sync. Relationship energy.\n- 💕 **Two Hearts** — Love between two people. Romantic, gentle, paired.\n- 🫶 **Heart Hands** — Appreciation, gratitude, \"sending love.\" Non-romantic warmth.\n\n---\n\nQuick cheat sheet:\n- ❤️ Romance | 💛 Bestie | 💙 Trust | 💜 Compassion | 🖤 Edgy cool | 🤍 Pure | 🧡 Warmth\n\nThere you go — now you can heart with precision 😄⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":578,"output":523,"cacheRead":63296,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64397,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774795105704}}
